# Commit Message Generation Rules

- Follow conventional commit message rule
- Commit message structure
    ```
    <Jira-ticket-ID>: <description>
    ```

- ALL message MUST be lower case
- MUST using `git status --porcelain` and `git diff --staged` to see what were changed
- SKIP exploring unnecessary files e.g. pnpm-lock.yaml, package-lock.json,...
- FOCUS on main file to understand what changes
- `description` MUST BE concise within 60 character (No more) but MUST cover all changes rather than only small part of changes
- MUST NOT add any notes or content beyond the structure above
- Give commit message in a code block so that user can easy to copy

# Check list
- Using `git status --porcelain` to see all files change, you can see the file names to understand the overview of what we did
- Using `git diff --staged` to understand the detail
- Summarize these changes about scope, what we did
- Generate commit message conver these changes

Examples:
✅ Good commit messages

```
geo-71: initialize project structure and config
```
```
geo-59: implement create new account functionality
```
```
geo-61: add login using email and password
```

❌ Bad commit messages
```
GEO-71: This commit initializes the project by setting up all the necessary configurations including tailwind, eslint, prettier, typescript, and other dependencies.
```
```
add login function and create user account
```
fix some stuff
```
```
geo-61: modified login.ts, added auth service, updated ui
```
```
geo-59: done
```
